[2] Cholera - Uganda (Kitgum)
Date: Thu, 1 Jun 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Monitor (Kampala)
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200606010941.html>

During the last 7 weeks, 8 internally displaced people died of
cholera in Kitgum district, according to the District Director of
Health Services, Dr Vincent Oringa.
He said on Mon, 29 May 2006, that at least 350 people had suffered
from cholera in 13 camps in the district. Oringa said 3 people died
in Putika IDP camp, 3 in Kitgum Town Council, 1 in Palabek Gem and 1
in Kitgum Matidi camp.
The first case of the disease was registered in Agoro on 16 May 2006
and spread to another 12 camps. Oringa said although the district had
suspended social functions like funeral rites and selling cooked food
items, people have not heeded to the call, which is a setback to
their effort in fighting the disease.
[Byline: Colombus Ono]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The map URL in the previous post shows the location of Kitgum
district in the northern part of Uganda bordering southern Sudan, the
location of the cholera outbreak. - Mod.LL]
