[3] Cholera - Angola
Date: Wed, 31 May 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and Angola Press Agency [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200606010853.html>

At least 32 new cases of cholera have been recorded from 27-31 May
2006 in Luanda, thus raising the number of cases from 137 to 169, but
no deaths have been recorded. The information is contained in a
daily report on the outbreak from the Provincial Health Delegation
distributed to Angop Wed, 31 May 2006.
Since the cholera outbreak was declared on 13 Feb 2006, 1515 people
have died in the country, out of 40 557 cases reported until 29 May
2006. Up to now, Luanda is the most affected province with 20 781
cases and 275 deaths, followed by Benguela (7671 cases), Malanje
(4018), Kwanza-Norte (3648), Bengo (2205), Kwanza-Sul (1012), Huila
(667), Lunda-Norte (215), Zaire (213). The least affected provinces
are: Uije (75), Cabinda (24), Huambo (15), Bie (13).
Soyo city, in northern Zaire province, recorded the first case of
cholera on Tue, 30 May 2006.
